 Lindy Hemming Talks Designing 007: Fifty Years of Bond Style 
		 
			 15 Jun ’12 11 Jan ’14   Lord Christopher Laverty Girls in Films ,  Guys in Films ,  Interviews ,  News 		 
	 
			 	
			

	 
		 Academy Award winning  costume designer Lindy Hemming has worked on five James Bond films with Pierce Brosnan and Daniel Craig in the lead role. Who better then to curate an exhibition of 007 style? The most anticipated event of its kind for fans of the Bond aesthetic, gadgets, sets, cars and some unforgettable costumes, this ambitious project has been in the making for nearly a decade. Speaking exclusively to  Clothes on Film , Lindy Hemming talks through her involvement with the exhibition and hints at what to expect